The how-to-build for the chatbot project:

1. Data Ingestion Pipeline
Important Steps:
 - Web Scrapping: Build a web-scraper to scrape the data from the web application(using Scrapy spiders 
 or BeautifulSoup or both, web page url: https://dubaigolf.com/) [NOTE: it must scrape all the data from the website in a Breadth-First Order].
 - Clean the Data: After extracting the data, create a python script to parse the content scrapped from the website or webpages and convert it to a machine-readable or RAG-ready file format.
 - Knowledge Base: Once the data has been cleaned, the data now can be used for building the knowledge base for the LLM to perform the RAG operation (or try using an LLM wiki).


2. Model Training Pipeline:
Important Steps:
 - Storing the data: Convert the data into vector(vector embedding) and store it in a vector database(Pinecone/ChromaDB or Neo4j for a free Graph Database)
 - Fetching the relevant data: With the help of FAISS or Hybrid Search, find data that is relevant to the query given by the user from the databse(use TFIDF).
 - Provide a few exmaples: Using Multi-Shot training and PEFT(Parameter-Efficient Training), fine-tune the LLM to show better performance and better accuracy in interacting with the user.
 - Evaluate the model: Using BLEU and ROUGE metrics, evaluate the Fine-Tuned LLM.

3. Frontend Application:(Must be done using streamlit)
Important Features:
 - Response Style: Define how the model must answer the customer based on the brief or detailed expalnation modes.
 - Chat Session: Maintain a chat session history to remember all the user interactions and also be able to create new chat sessions and store them in a cache.
 - Model Selection: The user can switch between the models that he/she prefers(the options will be between gpt-oss:20 and llama-3.1-70b-instruct).
 - User Feedback: After generating the response, display a rating scale along with the message: "How was the response" and a rating scale (typical 5 stars where the user can click on the star that he want to indicate the quality of the response generated). [NOTE: This feedback in turn will be used for retraining the model on user feedback. Hence create a database to store these feedbacks.]
 - Password Protected: The application will be protected by a simple password (no need for Authentication).


New Feature:
Admin Page: 
 - Admin Login Page: 
 	1. It should contain a username and password (stores the list of admins in a separate database different from the knowledge base and chat history)
	2. Once the credentials are entered, it must provide access to the knowledge base like updating the knowledge base, deleting data from the database etc (create a file that will be opened up in sqlite or any other sql application so that the user can download and make the changes)
	3. Include an upload option as well, so that the admin can update the knowledge base of the model.
	4. The changes that are not updated should be overwritten on the existing database.
	5. All of this should be done on streamlit.


